      "side": 1,
      "message": "So I have a general question about aliasing in D3D. What, if any, are the restrictions on using aliased memory within the same draws, render passes (if we ever use them), etc? I only ask because Vulkan has this same concept but I\u0027ve avoided it because there are a lot more restrictions and tracking that needs to be done with aliased memory.\n\nFor this specific use case with sRGB formats, but reading them as linear, does d3d12 not have a way to do this via views? In Vulkan when you create a VkImage with the flag VK_IMAGE_CREATE_MUTABLE_FORMAT_BIT which says that I can create GrVkImageViews of that Image with different formats.",
      "revId": "c36ccb6aef8c8cd95fdae2fc945451b767e0f6c8",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
